The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 SWC posts 16% sales growth

 A STAFF REPORTER

 Calcutta, Feb. 17: Shaw Wallace (SWC) has posted a 16 per cent growth in sales volume at 12.08 million cases in the first nine months ended December 31 against 10.4 million cases in the corresponding period last year.

 ?Focus on improving product mix and a shift towards brands that hold maximum value for the stakeholders have helped us deliver our best performance ever. The growth has been achieved in various segments despite increased competition,? said Prakash Nanani, chief operating officer ? Indian businesses, Jumbo Group. The industry growth for the period has been around 8 per cent.

 In the rationalisation exercise initiated early this financial year, Shaw Wallace had sharpened its focus on premium and top-selling brands in the deluxe segment, while phasing out some in the lower segment.

 Royal Challenge, the premium whisky, posted a sale of 1.21 lakh cases in December. Last year, Royal Challenge sold a million cases in a single year and the brand currently occupies over 65 per cent market share in the premium whisky segment. 

 Antiquity Rare Premium, the super premium whisky, has posted a growth of 40 per cent in the first nine months and occupies a market share of 92 per cent in the country.

 Director?s Special Black in the deluxe segment has witnessed a 70 per cent volume growth in the same period. 




